<h1>Particulars of Claim</h1>

<p><strong>Claimant:</strong> {{landlord_full_name}}</p>
<p><strong>Defendant:</strong> {{tenant_full_name}}</p>
<p><strong>Property:</strong> {{property_address}}</p>

<h2>Tenancy background</h2>
<p>
  The Defendant occupies the above property under an assured shorthold tenancy that commenced on
  {{tenancy_start_date}}. Rent is {{currency rent_amount}} per {{rent_frequency}}, payable in advance on
  the {{payment_day}} of each period.
</p>

<h2>Rent arrears</h2>
<p>
  The Defendant has failed to pay rent as it fell due. As at {{generation_date}}, the arrears total is
  {{currency arrears_total}}. A detailed schedule is attached and marked “Schedule of arrears”.
</p>

<h2>Property damage and other sums</h2>
{{#if damage_items.length}}
<p>The Defendant caused damage beyond fair wear and tear. The Claimant seeks:</p>
<ul>
  {{#each damage_items}}
  <li>{{description}} – {{currency amount}}</li>
  {{/each}}
</ul>
{{/if}}

{{#if other_charges.length}}
<p>Additional recoverable sums:</p>
<ul>
  {{#each other_charges}}
  <li>{{description}} – {{currency amount}}</li>
  {{/each}}
</ul>
{{/if}}

<h2>Interest</h2>
<p>
  The Claimant claims interest pursuant to section 69 County Courts Act 1984 at {{interest_rate}}% per annum
  from {{interest_start_date}} to {{generation_date}}, calculated at {{currency interest_to_date}}, and continuing at
  {{currency daily_interest}} per day until judgment or earlier payment.
</p>

<h2>Relief sought</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Arrears, damages and other sums totalling {{currency total_claim_amount}}</li>
  <li>Court fee of {{currency court_fee}}</li>
  {{#if solicitor_costs}}
  <li>Fixed legal costs of {{currency solicitor_costs}}</li>
  {{/if}}
  <li>Interest under section 69 CCA 1984</li>
</ol>

<h2>Statement of truth</h2>
